@node instructions "DMC-2-HTML - Instructions"
@{line}
@{b}Instructions@{ub}
@{line}
@{line}
The operation of this program should be fairly straightforward, but here are some brief instructions.
@{line}
@{line}
@{u}Converting a single file@{uu}
@{line}
Click on the button that says 'A file...' in the requester that asks you what you would like to convert. You will then be asked to select a source file (the DMC article) and then a destination file (the converted HTML). Once DMC-2-HTML has this information the conversion will take place.
@{line}
@{line}
@{u}Converting a directory@{uu}
@{line}
Click on the button that says 'A directory...'. You will be asked to select a source directory and then a destination directory. Once DMC-2-HTML has this information a progress window will be displayed showing you the number of files that have so far been converted.
@{line}
@{line}
Please note that DMC-2-HTML will not recurse into sub-directories.
@{line}
@endnode

@node faq "DMC-2-HTML - Frequently asked questions"
@{line}
@{b}Frequently asked questions@{ub}
@{line}
@{line}
@{b}Q.@{ub} @{i}Why is it that when I try to convert an article from a DMC disk magazine all I get is rubbish?@{ui}
@{line}
@{b}A.@{ub} Most DMC created disk magazines use CrunchMania to compress the articles to save disk space. You will need to either decrunch the files first or use CrunchMania's RTDD utility before starting DMC-2-HTML.
@{line}
@endnode

